ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The title of this Xinhuanet News Agency report, and its various
derivatives, is misleading. It has been established merely that the virus
isolated during the most recent outbreak of avian influenza in Anhui
province in China retains the antigenicity of the viruses previously
isolated throughout China and East Asia; i.e., the virus is a
highly-pathogenic strain of avian influenza A (H5N1) virus. Until the
nucleotide sequence of the complete genome of this new isolate has been
determined, little or nothing can be inferred about the genetic stability
of the virus causing outbreaks of avian influenza in China, and, elsewhere
in East Asia. - Mod.CP]
